sk.stuba.fiit.perconik.core.resources

Class DefaultResources

  • java.lang.Object
    • sk.stuba.fiit.perconik.core.resources.DefaultResources

  • public final class DefaultResources
extends java.lang.Object
    Static accessor methods pertaining to default resource core implementation.

    The core implementation includes default Resource instances along with respective ResourceNamesSupplier as well as default ResourceService, ResourceProvider and ResourceManager.

    The default implementations of resources as well as resource provider, manager and service are still available by this class even if the respective resources are unregistered from the core or the services are switched or stopped.

    Since:
    1.0
    Author:
    Pavol Zbell

    • Method Detail

      • getDefaultResourceProvider

        public static final ResourceProvider getDefaultResourceProvider()
        Returns the default resource provider. The returned provider is a standard resource provider constructed using the standard provider builder from ResourceProviders.builder() factory method. Its direct parent and the only predecessor in the resource provider hierarchy is the system resource provider.

        The default resource provider is lazily initialized at the first call of this method.

        Returns:
        the default resource provider
        See Also:
        ResourceProvider, ResourceProviders.builder(), ResourceProviders.getSystemProvider()

      • getDefaultResourceManager

        public static final ResourceManager getDefaultResourceManager()
        Returns the default resource manager. The returned manager is a standard resource manager constructed by the ResourceManagers.create() factory method.

        The default resource provider is lazily initialized at the first call of this method.

        Returns:
        the default resource manager
        See Also:
        ResourceManager, ResourceManagers.create()

      • getDefaultResourceService

        public static final ResourceService getDefaultResourceService()
        Returns the default resource service. The returned service is a standard resource service constructed using the standard service builder from ResourceServices.builder() factory method. It contains the default resource provider and manager.

        The default resource provider is lazily initialized at the first call of this method.

        Note: The returned service may be unusable if it has been retrieved by this method earlier and then stopped.

        Returns:
        the default resource service
        See Also:
        ResourceService, ResourceServices.builder(), getDefaultResourceProvider(), getDefaultResourceManager()

      • getDefaultResourceNamesSupplier

        public static final ResourceNamesSupplier getDefaultResourceNamesSupplier()
        Returns the default resource names supplier. The built supplier dynamically supplies resource names associated with listener types based on the currently used ResourceProvider obtained by this Services.getResourceService().getResourceProvider() method call at supplying.
        Returns:
        the default resource names supplier
        See Also:
        ResourceNamesSupplier, getDefaultResourceProvider()
